    INSERT INTO artwork (slug, artwork_name, artist_slug, price, size_in, size_cm, description, additional_information, material, medium, image)    VALUES ('imani-bilal-anew', 'anew', 'imani-bilal', '1850000', '72 × 60 × 2 in', '182.9 × 152.4 × 5.1 cm', 'None', '<p>Imani Bilal is a contemporary abstract painter and poet based in Jersey City, New Jersey. Her work is deeply inspired by the many states of the human condition and is rooted in her spiritual (Islamic) practices. As she explains, “I strive to convey the notion of Tawheed (oneness), the idea of primordial matter, chaos, and calm; of all things sharing a source and being connected to an infinite mound, inclusive of the human experience.”<br>Her language is versatile and her approach, unconventional, working with acrylic, ink, and resin to articulate emotion and promote connectivity through color and movement. Bilal, who has been experimenting with paint since childhood, has developed a unique process of her own. She often paints while seated on the floor to pour her whole body into the composition, using her hands, mouth, and found objects to create an array of effects that become part of an intricate yet fluid work of art.<br>Bilal’s first solo show in New York City, Fingerprints of Ruh (2020), curated by Nemo Librizzi, was met with enthusiasm and led to gallery representation by Chase Contemporary Gallery and recently, Mazlish Gallery.<br>Dubbed “a force to be reckoned with in the contemporary art world” by Forbes Magazine, her work has captivated many. Bilal says abstraction is rebellious by nature and fuels her artistic freedom. She is among a small community of Black Muslim American women who push the avant-garde.</p>', '''Intermedia; Multimedia work that does not fall into another category.''', '''Acrylic paint, ink & resin on canvas''', 'https://d7hftxdivxxvm.cloudfront.net?height=690&quality=80&resize_to=fit&src=https%3A%2F%2Fd32dm0rphc51dk.cloudfront.net%2F4hOWC7swf1xBJOC9gXhNDw%2Fnormalized.jpg&width=800')    
    INSERT INTO artwork (slug, artwork_name, artist_slug, price, size_in, size_cm, description, additional_information, material, medium, image)    VALUES ('charles-blackman-tea-break', 'tea break', 'charles-blackman', '30500.0', '16 1/2 × 23 1/5 in', '42 × 59 cm', 'None', '<p>Perhaps you have been to a party like &#39;Tea Break&#39;. Directly from Charles Blackman’s private collection, this charcoal drawing oozes style, featuring three figures complete with cigarette, skivvies and blunted fringes. You can almost hear the jazz. </p><p>As a member of Melbourne’s bohemian enclave, ‘Tea Break’ is surely drawn from Blackman’s life. It is an irreverent ode to friendship, conversation and beatnik reverie. </p><p>For collectors of modern art and important works on paper, ‘Tea Break’ is a captivating find. It is accompanied by a Certificate of Authenticity from the Charles Blackman Foundation. </p>', '''Includes collages; drawings; figure drawing; pen and ink; sketch. This also includes paintings where paper is the support.''', '''Charcoal on paper''', 'https://d7hftxdivxxvm.cloudfront.net?height=533&quality=80&resize_to=fit&src=https%3A%2F%2Fd32dm0rphc51dk.cloudfront.net%2Fny99RJ-PT7bgDboEnL761A%2Fnormalized.jpg&width=800')    
